{"TopicId":182127,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Quickest way to get to the Mun ?","CreatedByName":"Mountainjk","CreatedById":192954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T16:12:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mountainjk","CreatedById":192954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T16:12:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m always having trouble getting to the Mun(every planet in general too), I can land fine, Just its the part after orbit and before landing on target that I cant get.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone have any tips to help?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T18:32:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor planets, it gets tricky because you have to figure out the proper transfer\u00A0window (about once a year). You can\u0027t just go any old time you feel like it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the Mun, it should be pretty easy. You look where the Mun is, in its orbit around Kerbin. You aim 90 degrees ahead of that point. You burn prograde on the opposite side of Kerbin from your aim\u00A0point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Minmus, you aim 60 degrees ahead, instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mountainjk","CreatedById":192954,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T18:44:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549996354\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor planets, it gets tricky because you have to figure out the proper transfer\u00A0window (about once a year). You can\u0027t just go any old time you feel like it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the Mun, it should be pretty easy. You look where the Mun is, in its orbit around Kerbin. You aim 90 degrees ahead of that point. You burn prograde on the opposite side of Kerbin from your aim\u00A0point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Minmus, you aim 60 degrees ahead, instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, Thanks!\u00A0I\u0027ll try that. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kryxal","CreatedById":102688,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T19:47:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d call it more like 75 degrees to start for Mun, but in any case, it\u0027s easy with maneuver nodes.\u00A0 Drop the node, get the apoapsis you\u0027ll need, and slide the node around for a good intercept.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-12T20:07:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guide has not been updated for a while, but might still be helpful.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5959171704\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/116376-how-to-get-to-the-moons-with-an-example-sandbox-rocket-that-can-do-it/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:226px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gogi","CreatedById":168144,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-26T11:06:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223539530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221549996354\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/12/2019 at 7:32 PM, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor planets, it gets tricky because you have to figure out the proper transfer\u00A0window (about once a year). You can\u0027t just go any old time you feel like it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the Mun, it should be pretty easy. You look where the Mun is, in its orbit around Kerbin. You aim 90 degrees ahead of that point. You burn prograde on the opposite side of Kerbin from your aim\u00A0point.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Minmus, you aim 60 degrees ahead, instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually you can go at any time. It just won\u0027t be efficient.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-26T13:51:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223547522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551179192\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168144\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gogi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Gogi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually you can go at any time. It just won\u0027t be efficient.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh. Well, just try to get to Jool when it\u0027s on the wrong side of the Sun. It\u0027ll take at least 25 km/s of deltaV. Which is a bit more than just \u0022inefficient\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoatRider","CreatedById":103681,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-26T14:27:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223547564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551189086\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh. Well, just try to get to Jool when it\u0027s on the wrong side of the Sun. It\u0027ll take at least 25 km/s of deltaV. Which is a bit more than just \u0022inefficient\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot as bad as some old science fiction novels would have you do it- burn at 1G until you\u0027re halfway there, and then turn around and burn at 1G until you get there. My calculus is too rusty to calculate\u00A0how much DeltaV that would take.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-26T15:00:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223547577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551191254\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103681\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GoatRider\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, GoatRider said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot as bad as some old science fiction novels would have you do it- burn at 1G until you\u0027re halfway there, and then turn around and burn at 1G until you get there. My calculus is too rusty to calculate\u00A0how much DeltaV that would take.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n10m/s for each second of the journey. Time = 2 * sqrt(distance in meters / 10).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut at least you can be sure there will be no physical low-G degradation. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-02-26T15:02:17Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2019 03:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by bewing\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Espatie","CreatedById":194327,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-26T15:11:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe maneuver node for a Mun transfer from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E is at roughly the point at which the Mun appears to rise over Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoatRider","CreatedById":103681,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-26T16:25:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223547596\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551193221\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n10m/s for each second of the journey. Time = 2 * sqrt(distance in meters / 10).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n21,900 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E for the Mun. It\u0027s not quite as bad as I thought.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"miletran168","CreatedById":195857,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-02T19:00:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E21.900\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;border-bottom:none;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Echo Mun it so long.\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-03T00:57:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223550456\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551553231\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022195857\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022miletran168\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, miletran168 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cfont style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E21.900\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;border-bottom:none;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont style=\u0022vertical-align:inherit;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Echo Mun it so long.\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forums. That number is for a constant 1G trip -- which is impossible in the game without cheating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gogi","CreatedById":168144,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T11:35:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223547564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182127\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551189086\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/26/2019 at 2:51 PM, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh. Well, just try to get to Jool when it\u0027s on the wrong side of the Sun. It\u0027ll take at least 25 km/s of deltaV. Which is a bit more than just \u0022inefficient\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it is possible \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T18:08:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother way to think of it which might make sense to you is to imagine things like positions on a clock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn map mode, look at your orbit and Kerbin from above.\u00A0\u00A0 Rotate the view until the Mun is at 3 o\u0027clock. Place your maneuver node at 6 o\u0027clock.\u00A0\u00A0 Pull the prograde marker, simulating a \u0022forward\u0022 burn (\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:prograde:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/prograde3.png\u0022 title=\u0022:prograde:\u0022\u003E).\u00A0 You will intercept the Mun at 12 o\u0027clock each and everytime.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}